  "prompt": "What would you do if your girlfriend asks for money?",
  "response": "If your girlfriend asks for money, it\u2019s important to handle the situation thoughtfully and consider a few factors:\n\n1. **Understand the Reason**: Ask her why she needs the money. Understanding her situation can provide clarity and help you determine the appropriate response.\n\n2. **Evaluate your Relationship**: Consider the nature of your relationship. Is it built on trust and mutual support? Think about whether this is a one-time request or part of a pattern.\n\n3. **Financial Boundaries**: Reflect on your own financial situation and set boundaries. Only offer what you are comfortable giving or lending. It's important to protect your own financial wellbeing.\n\n4. **Discuss Options**: If you're not comfortable giving money, consider discussing other ways you might be able to support her, whether it's helping her budget, finding resources, or exploring alternatives.\n\n5. **Be Honest**: If you decide not to give her money, communicate your feelings honestly and respectfully. It\u2019s important for both partners to have open discussions about finances.\n\n6. **Set Clear Terms**: If you do decide to lend her money, establish clear terms regarding repayment to avoid misunderstandings later.\n\nUltimately, trust and communication are crucial in any relationship, especially when it comes to finances.",
